main event: Capt. McLauchlan reported seeing a silver-white sphere much higher than a jet fighter at Lake Kisukongo, Wisconsin, estimated at 5000 feet on July 23, 1952.
interesting points: The object turned 180 degrees and changed shape from spherical to elliptical during the turn., The speed of the object was estimated to be five times that of a jet aircraft., The duration of the sighting was approximately 5 minutes., The observer was Capt. Neil H. McLauchlan, USAF, Medical Corps., The sighting occurred under perfectly clear weather conditions.
witness description: Capt. Neil H. McLauchlan, USAF, Medical Corps
